HOUSE BILL No. 1018
_____
DIGEST OF HB 1018 (Updated February 9, 2026 10:34 am - DI 140)
Citations Affected: IC 12-17.
Synopsis: School age child care. Removes certain transportation
requirements in the approval criteria for the school age child care
project fund. Requires the division of family resources to adopt rules
specifying cost and expense standards for transporting a child to a
facility where the child does not attend school.
Effective: July 1, 2026.
DeVon, Goss-Reaves, Olthoff
(SENATE SPONSORS — DONATO, WALKER G)
December 1, 2025, read first time and referred to Committee on Family, Children and
Human Affairs.
January 14, 2026, reported — Do Pass.
January 20, 2026, read second time, ordered engrossed.
January 21, 2026, engrossed.
January 22, 2026, read third time, passed. Yeas 93, nays 0.
SENATE ACTION
January 26, 2026, read first time and referred to Committee on Family and Children
Services.
February 9, 2026, reported favorably — Do Pass.
